<P>The <B>ABC</B>ï¿½s &amp; <B>DE</B>ï¿½s of Computer Health and Safety</P>

<P>&#9;ï¿½<B>A</B>wareness</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½<B>B</B>reaks</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½<B>C</B>arriage/Posture</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½(<B>D</B>eadly)Radiation</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½<B>E</B>yes</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½<B>F</B>urniture</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>
<B><P>A</B>wareness</P>

<P>&#9;ï¿½Computers can be dangerous to your health</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;Eyes, wrists, arms, back, neck</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;Why?  What causes problems?</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;&#9;(Pascarelli &amp; Quilter, RSI)</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;&#9;Repetition</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;&#9;Ignorance</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;&#9;Strained &amp; Constrained  Posture</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;&#9;Holding still</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;&#9;A deconditioned workforce</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;&#9;Forced speed</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;&#9;Incentive programs &amp; overtime</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;&#9;Excessive monitoring</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;Not quite a complete list&#9;&#9;</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Most important thing to remember</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>
<B><P>B</B>reaks</P>

<P>&#9;ï¿½Best protection against dangers</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Moderate activity--15 minutes/2 hours</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Intensive activity-- 15 minutes/1 hour</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Get up, Non-computer work, Relax</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Exercises</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Ergonomic software</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>
<B><P>C</B>arriage/Posture</P>

<P>&#9;ï¿½Wrists--straight in both dimensions</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Wrist rests, braces</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Forearms--parallel to floor</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Thighs--parallel to floor</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Feet--flat on floor, footrest</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Back--straight</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Adjust furniture, Exercises</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½CTD--cumulative trauma disorders</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½RSI--repetitive stress injuries</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Computer athlete</P>

<P>Seven P's (Pascarelli &amp; Quilter, RSI)</P>

<P>&#9;ï¿½Physician</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Pain Management</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Posture</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Preventive exercises</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Positioning</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Pacing</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Patience</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>(<B>D</B>eadly) Radiation</P>

<P>&#9;ï¿½Health effects of monitor radiation--debatable</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Probably not deadly, but some evidence of problems</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Monitor should meet MPRII guidelines</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½2.5 feet from front of monitor</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½4.0 feet from side and back of monitor</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Powerdown when not using monitor</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Pregnant women should take special precautions</P>
<P>&#9;</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>
<B><P>E</B>yes</P>

<P>&#9;ï¿½Eye examination by an eye care professional</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Refocus for 5-10 seconds every 10 minutes</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Copy stand</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Glasses</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Lighting, Glare</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Visual Ergonomics--Ankrum</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;www.ur-net.com/office-ergo/setting.htm</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>
<B><P>F</B>urniture</P>

<P>&#9;ï¿½Chair, adjustable</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Table, desk--height</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Foot rest</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Copy holder, copy stand</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Foot rest</P>
<P>&#9;ï¿½Wrist rest</P>
<P><BR>
